Atomic radial potentials for 1 <= Z <= 118 from non-relativistic
atomic LDA exchange-only calculations with spin-restricted orbitals
and spherically symmetric densities as described in

S. Lehtola, "Fully numerical calculations on atoms with fractional
occupations. Range-separated exchange functionals", arXiv:1908.02528.

using accurate 10-element finite-element calculations as described in

S. Lehtola, "Fully numerical Hartree-Fock and density functional
calculations. I. Atoms", Int. J. Quantum Chem. 119, e25945 (2019).
DOI: 10.1002/qua.25945

to be used in combination with the Superposition of Atomic Potentials
initial guess that was described in

S. Lehtola, "Assessment of Initial Guesses for Self-Consistent Field
Calculations. Superposition of Atomic Potentials: Simple yet
Efficient", J. Chem. Theory Comput. 15, 1593 (2019).
DOI: 10.1021/acs.jctc.8b01089


2019-11-20
Susi Lehtola
